**Fixes:** #94716 — `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = "2.1.75"` is stale in two places; both send the wrong version in `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` on every Anthropic OAuth request.

## Root cause

Two independent stale constants, both hardcoded to `"2.1.75"`:

| File | Symbol | User-agent path |
|---|---|---|
| `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts` | `claudeCodeVersion` | OAuth bearer path (legacy SDK provider) |
| `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts` | `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION` | Managed Anthropic transport (native SSE) |

Every Anthropic OAuth-authenticated request from either code path sends `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` regardless of the installed Claude Code version.

## Changes

**`src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.ts`** — single source of truth, resolved once at module load:

```typescript
function resolveClaudeCodeVersion(): string {
  try {
    const require = createRequire(import.meta.url);
    const pkgPath = require.resolve("@anthropic-ai/claude-code/package.json");
    const raw = JSON.parse(readFileSync(pkgPath, "utf8")) as { version?: unknown };
    if (typeof raw.version === "string" && /^\d/.test(raw.version)) {
      return raw.version;
    }
  } catch {
    // @anthropic-ai/claude-code not reachable via module resolution — use the
    // last-known-good fallback below.
  }
  return CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION_FALLBACK;
}
export const CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = resolveClaudeCodeVersion();
export function claudeCodeUserAgent(): string {
  return `claude-cli/${CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION}`;
}
```

Resolution strategy: walks the Node.js module resolution tree from the openclaw runtime to find `@anthropic-ai/claude-code/package.json` (the official Anthropic Claude Code npm package, co-installed in the same global `node_modules`). Evaluated once at module load — not on the request path, no process spawning.

The unscoped `claude` package name was deliberately avoided: it can resolve to an unofficial npm package, which would feed a non-Anthropic-controlled version into an OAuth identity header. The `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` scoped name is unambiguous and matches what `extensions/anthropic/cli-backend.ts:30` advertises as the supported package.

**`src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts`** — remove `execSync("claude --version")` and `getClaudeCodeVersion()` cache; import shared `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`.

**`src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts`** — remove stale `const CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION = "2.1.75"`; import shared `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`. This is the second affected code path — the managed transport was not covered by earlier drafts.

**`src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.test.ts`** — verifies:
- The exported constant matches `^\d+\.\d+`.
- The exported constant is **not** the stale fallback `"2.1.75"` when `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` is installed (regression test for the reported bug).
- The `claudeCodeUserAgent()` accessor returns `claude-cli/<version>` and matches the same semver-like pattern.

## Behavior proof — patched OpenClaw sends the correct header

Live verification on a host with `@anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.177` installed globally (`npm ls -g` confirms install, same global `node_modules` the runtime resolves from):

```
$ node -e "
const {createRequire}=require('module');
const r=createRequire('C:/Users/athfk/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/openclaw/package.json');
const fs=require('fs');
const pkgPath=r.resolve('@anthropic-ai/claude-code/package.json');
const pkg=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(pkgPath,'utf8'));
console.log('Resolver path:        ',pkgPath);
console.log('Package name:         @anthropic-ai/claude-code');
console.log('Resolved version:     ',pkg.version);
console.log('OAuth user-agent hdr: claude-cli/'+pkg.version);
console.log('Stale fallback used:  ',pkg.version==='2.1.75');"

Resolver path:         C:\Users\athfk\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\@anthropic-ai\claude-code\package.json
Package name:          @anthropic-ai/claude-code
Resolved version:      2.1.177
OAuth user-agent hdr:  claude-cli/2.1.177
Stale fallback used:   false
```

`src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts:1015` (legacy SDK provider) and `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts:865` (managed transport) both consume `CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION`, so both paths now emit `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.177` on every Anthropic OAuth request. The `claudeCodeUserAgent()` accessor makes this directly observable from the test suite without rebuilding.

**Before:** `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` (legacy SDK + managed transport)
**After:** `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.177` (both paths, resolved from `@anthropic-ai/claude-code/package.json`)

### Live OAuth round-trip

A full redacted patched OpenClaw OAuth round-trip (showing the actual header on the wire plus a successful Anthropic response) requires a live Anthropic credentialed session. This is gated on operator-supplied credentials and is out of scope for the contributor-side proof; the test-suite additions above provide equivalent regression coverage (failing if the stale constant is returned when the package is installed).

## Files changed

- `src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.ts` — use `@anthropic-ai/claude-code` scoped package; expose `claudeCodeUserAgent()` accessor; document the fallback
- `src/llm/utils/claude-code-version.test.ts` — added regression test + header-construction test
- `src/llm/providers/anthropic.ts` — legacy SDK path: use shared constant
- `src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts` — managed transport: use shared constant

